					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79090052" rend="visible">
						<summary>A service book, according to the Yemenite rite, with the books of Psalms and Proverbs prefixed.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb"> </textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n79090052">
							<locus from="1r" to="155v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sidur</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">סדור</title>
							<note>
								<p>The bulk of the manuscript (folios 33-138) is dated <date calendar="Hebrew">1961</date> (<date calendar="Gregorian">1650</date>), and the prefixed and appended portions were probably written a little later.</p>
							</note>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">שלים בסיועתא דשמיא בחד בשבא דהוא <date calendar="Seleucid">תלתה יומין לירח אב יהפך לששון שנת אתתקס"א לשטרי'</date> ספרא קלא חיים באמ' <name type="person" role="scribe">שלום בן דוד בן יצחק בן שלמה ן' יעקב הידוע אלחגאני</name> אלהים יזכיני להרבות ספרים עד אין קץ כי"ר ונכתב על שם החבר הטוב והנעים [ילד] שעשועים נטע נעמנים בן הנאמנים <name type="person" role="patron">יהודה בן מש[ה] בן סעדיה אלצנעאני אללוי</name> יש"ל אלהים יזכהו להגות בו וכו'. <locus n="138v"/>
							</colophon>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="26r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Psalms</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="26r" to="34v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Proverbs</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="34v" to="42r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for week-days</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="42r" to="50r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for the Sabbath</title>
							<filiation>Cf the contents of Or 2418, part II.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="50r" to="51r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for rosh ḥodesh</title>
							<filiation>Cf the contents of Or 2418, part III.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="51r" to="57r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Pesaḥ</title>
							<filiation>Cf the contents of Or 2418, part IV.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="57r" to="61v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Shavu῾ot</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="61v" to="62r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Prayer for the fast days</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="62r" to="76v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Tish῾ah be-av</title>
							<note>
								<p>The book of Lamentations begins on folio 62v. The book of Job is also given at the end of this part.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="76v" to="79v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Rosh ha-Shanah</title>
							<filiation>Cf the contents of Or 2418, part VIII.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="79v" to="86r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Yom Kipur</title>
							<filiation>Cf the contents of Or 2418, part IX.</filiation>
							<note>
								<p>At the end of this part is Keter malkhut of <name type="person" role="author">Solomon ibn Gabirol</name>.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="86r" to="93r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Sukot</title>
							<filiation>Cf the services and hosh῾anot in Or 2418, part X, and Or 1480, part .</filiation>
							<note>
								<p>In the margin around the haḳafot there are pieces beginning in each case with 'raḥmana'.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="93r" to="95r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Ḥanukah</title>
							<filiation>Cf the content of Or 2418, part XI.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="95r" to="95v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Purim</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="95v" to="96r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Tseloah almiyat</title>
							<filiation>Cf the content of Or 2418, part XIII.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="96r" to="101r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Seliḥot le-lele ashmurot</title>
							<filiation>Cf the content of Or 2418, part XIV.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="101r" to="119v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Seliḥot le-el raḥamim</title>
							<filiation>Cf the content of Or 2389, XVI.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="119v" to="123r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Seder ῾avodah</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/90633023">Ibn Ezra, Abraham ben Meïr, 1089-1164</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/90633023">אבן עזרא, אברהם בן מאיר, 1089-1164</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="123r" to="127v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Berakhot</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="127v" to="132v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">῾Ibur ha-shanim</title>
							<note>
								<p>Tables of cycles 285-287 are given in full, the manuscript having been written in the first year of maḥzor 285 (<date calendar="Gregorian">1650</date>). Calculations for the different kinds of years follow.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="132v" to="135r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Nusaḥ ha-ketubot, ha-giṭin ṿeha-sheṭarot</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="135r" to="138v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Liturgical pieces</title>
							<filiation>Cf the content of Or 2418.</filiation>
							<note>
								<p>Includes Tokhaḥot u-vaḳashot and Shirot ṿe-tishbaḥot.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="139r" to="15v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Additions</title>
							<note>
								<p>A number of appended sections, written in various hands: folio 139r sqq. - Nusaḥ ha-sha῾anon, folio 144v sqq. - Poetical pieces; folio 153r sqq. - Tokhaḥot  ṿe-azharot.</p>
								<p>Between these appended sections there are five of additional poetical pieces and petitions, all more all less damaged.</p>
								<p>Folio 155 contains Birkat ha-levanah.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>155 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>280</height>
										<width>185</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>235</height>
										<width>145</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>155 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end).</p>
									<p>Folios 1-33 have a separate Hebrew foliation (from 63 onwards, folios 34-95 being numbered 1-62).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 8 leaves each, marked by catchwords at the end (mostly not preserved).</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Leaves stuck on paper (modern restoration).</p>
									<p>Folios damaged at the beginning and at the end.</p>
									<p>Lacuna after folio 95.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 2" ruledLines="31" writtenLines="31">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Visible mastara ruling.</p>
									<p>Initial words written in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Leaf catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>Numerous marginal notes and additions.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Yemenite semi-cursive script of the 17th century, puctuated.  Shalom ben Daṿid ben Yitsḥaḳ ben Shelomoh ben Ya῾aḳov Al-Ḥag᾿ani: inscribed, folio 138v.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
